			<section>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>DealTapp</strong></h3>
					<p>Connecting users with local businesses</p>
				</header>
				<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
					<p>DealTapp is an app that lets users to find the best deals at local restaurants, cafes, and entertainment venues.</p>
					<p>The app gives power to small and local shops by giving them control over the deals they offer. It also makes it easy for users to claim these deals. Deals range from a discounted coffee to free event tickets.</p>
				</div>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>Building a Company</strong></h3>
					</header>
					<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
						<p>DealTapp is a new app with tons of potential. This makes for a really exciting culture. As the only designer for DealTapp, I have huge influence over the direction of the app and I get to wear many hats. Aside from my responsibilites as a UX Designer, I discuss decisions with the founders, take photographs, test the software, meet with newspaper reporters, and interview potential employees.</p>
						<p>I love being a part of this enviroment. Every time we meet I am able to work on something new and gain new experiences. I've seen how I must adapt my methods to fit the resources of the company. I enjoy the highs and learn from the lows.</p>
					</div>
			</section>
			<header class="major special">
				<h2>Step One</h2>
			</header>

			<section>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>Building a Design Culture</strong></h3>
					<p>Being the lead UX Designer</p>
				</header>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="8u$ 12u$(medium)">
						<p>The first thing I did as a designer was document everything. This helps me get to know the app and understand the reasons behind decisions.</p>
						<p>At DealTapp I want to take responsibility for all design decisions. I also want to show the value of design to the founders. In order to build a design culture I need to get them on board by showing them something concrete. After documenting everything, I did an initial round of user testing. I wanted to uncover the main usability issues so that I could fix them. Doing this will give me concrete examples of problems and solutions to present to the founders.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
