			<header class="major special">
				<h2>Step Two</h2>
			</header>
			<section>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>User Testing</strong></h3>
					<p>Uncovering the top usuability issues</p>
				</header>
				<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
					<p>I started out by testing the recommended five users. <a href="https://www.nngroup.com/articles/why-you-only-need-to-test-with-5-users/" class="inline-link">Source.</a> This helped maximize the budget by uncovering the top usuability issues without using too many resources.</p>
					<p>The main issues I found were:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>The location of the sign up/sign in feature was not intuituve.</li>
						<li>The overall purpose of the app was not clear enough.</li>
						<li>Redeeming a deal was a pain point.</li>
						<li>The menu icon was not conventional.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</section>

